    Note over Konflux,Dashboard: Flow 1: Build-Time Metadata Extraction & Catalog Generation

    Konflux->>Extractor: Trigger build pipeline<br/>odh-model-metadata-collection-v3-2-on-push

    Extractor->>FS: Load models-index.yaml<br/>& validated-models-index.yaml

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Extractor,HF: HuggingFace Enrichment (Optional)
        Extractor->>HF: GET /api/collections<br/>TLS 1.2+, No Auth (Public)
        HF-->>Extractor: Collection data (model list)
        Extractor->>HF: GET /api/models/{model_id}<br/>TLS 1.2+, No Auth
        HF-->>Extractor: Model details, tags
        Extractor->>HF: GET /{model_id}/raw/main/README.md<br/>TLS 1.2+, No Auth
        HF-->>Extractor: README content + YAML frontmatter
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over Extractor,RHIO: OCI Registry Extraction (Required)
        Extractor->>RHIO: GET /v2/{image}/manifests/{tag}<br/>TLS 1.2+, Docker Credentials
        RHIO-->>Extractor: Container manifest + annotations
        Extractor->>RHIO: GET /v2/{image}/blobs/{digest}<br/>TLS 1.2+, Docker Credentials
        RHIO-->>Extractor: Modelcard layer<br/>(io.opendatahub.modelcar.layer.type: modelcard)
    end

    Extractor->>Extractor: Parse modelcard markdown<br/>Extract YAML frontmatter<br/>Regex pattern matching
    Extractor->>Extractor: Enrich: match registry models<br/>to HuggingFace models
    Extractor->>Extractor: Generate catalog:<br/>deduplicate, merge static data
    Extractor->>FS: Write models-catalog.yaml<br/>& validated-models-catalog.yaml

    Note over Docker,Container: Container Image Build

    Docker->>Docker: COPY catalog files to /app/data/
    Docker->>Container: Build ubi9-minimal image<br/>Multi-arch: amd64, arm64, ppc64le, s390x<br/>User: 1001 (non-root)

    Note over Container,Dashboard: Flow 2: Runtime Data Delivery

    Container->>Container: sleep infinity<br/>(static data container)
    Dashboard->>Container: Volume mount /app/data/<br/>Read catalog YAML files
    Container-->>Dashboard: models-catalog.yaml<br/>validated-models-catalog.yaml
